nodes.title: Notes
widgets_values:
Recommended upscalers:
1. NMKD Artisofject: https://nmkd.de/shared/?dir=ESRGAN/Models/Realistic%2C%20Multipurpose
2. Remacri: https://openmodeldb.info/models/4x-Remacri
3. Real_HAT_GAN: https://github.com/XPixelGroup/HAT

Tips:
1. To increase the final image size, you need to modify the Upscale Image By values.
2. If you want more variation from your image, you need to increase the denoise of the Detailer or Ultimate SD Upscale.
3. If you want more detail while maintaining consistency, you need to increase the Detailer Passes, which is currently set to 2.

Requirements:
1. Checkpoint CyberRealistic: https://civitai.com/models/15003?modelVersionId=256915
2. Lora SDXLRender: https://civitai.com/models/171159/sdxlrender

To use the SDXL workflow, you must set the Tile Size value of the "Load Image" node to 768, and the Tile Size value of the "Ultimate SD Upscale - SAG" node to 1024.

In the "Ultimate SD Upscale - SAG" node, you will see the "Select Image" option. The value 1 corresponds to the unscaled version, and the value 2 corresponds to the upscaled version. For example, if your initial image is 768x768, if you choose the value 1, your final version will be 3072x3072 and 6144x6144. If you choose the value 2, your final image will be 6144x6144 and 12288x12288.
